course_metadata.title: Application of circular economy principles in structural design

content_chunks.content: This digital course introduces students to the principles of circular economy in structural design and construction. It focuses on sustainable approaches to structural engineering, including life cycle assessment, material reuse, and innovative strengthening techniques for recycled structures. The course combines theoretical knowledge with practical applications, emphasizing environmental impact reduction and resource efficiency in construction.

Circular economy technology for sustainable structural design and resource-efficient construction - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in implementing circular economy principles through lifecycle assessment, material reuse strategies, and innovative reinforcement techniques for recycled structures. Students master environmental impact analysis methods, construction material recycling protocols, and design for disassembly principles that maximize resource efficiency and minimize waste. The curriculum covers structural strengthening techniques, material recovery systems, regulatory frameworks for sustainable construction, and solutions for retrofitting recycled structures. Graduates emerge skilled in applying circular design solutions that transform traditional construction practices into environmentally responsible systems while maintaining structural integrity and performance through innovative engineering approaches and comprehensive sustainability methodologies.
